	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you're going to DoT kite - and you need to med while doing so, here is a method to use (you should probably have ensnare for this):<br>1) for mobs without a speed buff (guards, Ulrich McMannus, many creatures), you can ensnare, DoT, then run with sow for a 10 count, med for a 10 count, then see where your target is.<br>2) for creatures with a speed buff (giants, griffons), ensnare, DoT, run for a 10 count, med for a 6 count, see where your target is.<br>This method is not recommended for shadowed men, werewolves,or GrimFeather. Amongst others, to be sure. You can probably still get away with it if you're kiting werewolves, but in my experience - those guys are quick. You can ensnare a shadowed man, run with sow for about 10 seconds and still not have time to cast before he catches you. They have a natural SoC or something.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
