<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96756331016865></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96756331016865><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=96756331016865>RE: Tanking Druids</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=96756331016865#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=759><span id=Scholar>Adiemus</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>63 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Aug 29th 11:35 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.75]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>You raised a good point, Rianne.<br><br>It is indeed worth keeping your melee skills maxxed out, preferably in 1hs, 1hb and 2hb (if you're going to skip one, skip 2hb- wisdom-adding item should be caried in off-hand at all times) for the very reason you stated. In addition, some MoBs, notably the gnolls outside Paw, will, in essence, give up when taken down to about a half-bub of health and just stand there waiting to die.&nbsp;&nbsp;This happens only if they are snared/ensnared, BTW. Yes, you could nuke em again to kill, but its also a great time to work on your weapon skills with little or no risk to yourself. So go for it- it'll take longer, but you're a better rounded character with those melee skills up.<br><br>Also, I tend to practice weapon skills in a group. I ask if folks mind me going melee and caution them that I'll mete out very low damage as opposed to my nukes/DoTs. I also remind them that this saves mana for healing and buffs. If they don't mind, then I wade in occasionally; if they do, no worries- I still do my job ensnaring/dotting/healing. This tactic also allows you to practice melee skills in a reduced-threat situation- always the best time.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
