<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96757923010331></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96757923010331><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=96757923010331>RE: After 25?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=96757923010331#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Aug 29th 4:00 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Get your butt to Kunark and camp the Forest Giants in Warsliks Woods. Their level ranges are from mid teens to about 27, you can kite them along the trails because they have low magic resist, PLUS they have a rare drop - the forest loop (worth about 1,000 - 1,300pp). They're a constant spawn, and you'll level quickly. Usually, Warsliks isn't heavily camped because its tough to get to - so print out a few maps from eqatlas, and keep that SoW fresh. You can bind yourself there, port to sell and gate back. I'm lvl 27 now, but I'm sticking with giants until I hit level 29 or until I get another Loop. (already got one).<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
