	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.67]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have found that soloing in Nagafens Lair is possible for druids, if you know how...<br><br>By casting a root spell (engulfing root if you have it,a different one if you dont) then casting a DoT spell on Kobolds will slowly take down around half of their health before the DoT runs out,and all you have to do is keep the root spell going every 20 seconds or so (so it doesnt accidently run out when your medding).<br><br>The benifits are that you can med in between castings, so 1 kill only takes about 2 bubbles of mana and you get nice exp in return, and since your hunting alone the loot and exp is yours and yours alone,no need to share.<br><br>Also if you have Allure of the Wind you can cast it on sonic bats and have them fight for you, as they are more powerfull than kobolds you will get great exp for no work but 1 spell. (Only use Allure, anything else will be resisted to often and you will surely die)<br><br>Hope these help. <br><br>Aaja, lvl 50 Druid on Terris-Thule<br>Atothy, lvl 35 Rouge on Terris-Thule<br>Silvermyst,lvl 20 Enchanter Terris-Thule<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
