<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96725748024026></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96725748024026><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=96725748024026>RE: Getting beat on while in a group?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=96725748024026#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=759><span id=Scholar>Adiemus</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>63 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Aug 25th 10:38 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.80]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Good call, especially if Indoors.<br><br>If outdoors and grouped, let me suggest an alternative. <br><br>GET THE MOB'S ATTENTION AND HOLD IT!<br><br>No,I haven't lost my mind (OK...bets are on both sides of that one). If you, the Druid, pulled the MoB by Ensnare/Snare, DD it a couple of times so that it will single you out for special attention. Back away from the MoB at a leisurely pace, making sure that it futilely pursues you. The tanks in your group should NOT taunt, but rather proceed to wail away on the back of the MoB as it doggedly attempts to kill it's tormentor. You might have to nuke it again occasionally, as a good smack by a tank or caster might divert its attention, but this tactic generally results in a dead mob, several virtually undamaged tanks, and only the downtime necessary for the Druid to regain a couple bubs of mana. If you really want a Utopian experience, get into a group with TWO druids and have them take turns pulling and then medding. Virtually NO downtime then!<br><br>Personal experience: my 34 pally and his 38 druid buddy regularly kill griffons/hill giants/sand giants using this tactic. If we can persuade another tank to join us, we can average a kill every 3-5 minutes or so, with about 2 minutes downtime between fights for medding. Call it 8 kills per hour, netting around 200pp loot and a bit less than a&nbsp;&nbsp;bub or so xp for each. My 31 Druid introduced this tactic to many groups in SK at the gnolls, and all are astounded at the benefits of taking little damage and putting MoBs down quickly. <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
